    "ML training with simulated data alone has been done in research fields where observation data are fundamentally scarce, such as in the cases of tsunamis (Makinoshima et al. 2021) and gravity waves (Licciardi et al. 2022).",
    "The emulation of ground motions using ML surrogate models, such as generative ML models, PINNs, and neural operators, is expected to be used for data augmentation.",
    "Another approach to address this issue is incorporating geophysical findings into the ML model.",
    "Several studies have incorporated conventional GMPEs into the ML model.",
    "Es are stable for extrapolation or low data density because conventional GMPEs are based on the geophysical background of ground motions."
  ],
